Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Defect Modular Bootstrap", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9853503078088207`*^9, 
  3.985350313726358*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0776f0a0-ed71-4d8f-90dd-\
1fd383b81ded"],

Cell["\<\
When the modular matrix has degeneracies modular bootstrap can only do so \
much to predict the the topological lines of the theory. Here we use a \
version of Breadth First Search to resolve the ambiguities.\
\>", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98535031852282*^9, 3.985350322932889*^9}, {
  3.985350354330689*^9, 
  3.985350448189599*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4b479006-7184-4aad-9b94-\
3a8e031e3555"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Modular Bootstrap", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.985350452586651*^9, 3.9853504693501043`*^9}, 
   3.985771768599184*^9},ExpressionUUID->"01ac1b70-84cb-49dc-a14e-\
864c37ae1a60"],

Cell["\<\
We will do this example on the folded Tricritical Ising CFT, but the \
parameters will be documented so that one can change them.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.985350510893055*^9, 
  3.9853505427260103`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d2846055-7ffb-4877-98ba-\
fac709948cc5"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Defining Folded Tricritical Ising Modular Data ", "Subsection",
